<br>
A) Avoidance AC<br>
<br>
B) Skills<br>
<br>
Avoidance AC translates simply into a miss.  The EQ engine hasnt displayed our avoidance AC since beta, but if you dump about 9000 copper on yourself you can get a pretty good idea (All lost AC from encumberance/monk weight limit is avoidance type).  This is partially why high monk ac is misleading to other classes...a few hundred points of that is avoidance, NOT mitigation.  <br>
<br>
Skills are just that.  You make a roll, if you make it the skill activates.  Block/riposte/dodge/etc..<br>
<br>
So in closing, the only way you can really avoid getting hit more is via skill modifiers (such as the 10 percent to block bracer from Griegs end) and max agility (255) once you're lvl 60 and all your skills are maxed. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unorpin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Norpin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grand High Poobah</span><br>  Posts: 3837<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/26/02 2:07:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=31239.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Not Getting Hit.</span><hr size=1> &quot;What does it take for a monk To avoid a attack?  I would Say first Defense, then block, riposte, and dodge. And after all these Armour class.&quot;<br>
